<subSubSection id="5E576B6EB8B315B328D302EF4B4AC184" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="52D386FD00F6DBD6E3B4FC93E6825406" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Status. Native to Black Sea Basin, invasive in Caspian Sea, introduced in Aral Sea but extinct there.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CBA6BA2BE9167CA3F357EF841703B68" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6C7D37479AE77F271C4EA278F0ACF643" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Type locality. Sicily, Italy.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD0D553AFF69B6AD3036974074752ED8" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Distribution. Native to the Mediterranean and Black Sea. Introduced in the Caspian Sea between 1917 and 1919 (
<bibRefCitation id="372B77F21AAFF92DDECE0A426B472E7A" author="Grigorovich, IA" journalOrPublisher="Biological Invasions" pageId="75" pageNumber="106" pagination="103 - 115" title="History of aquatic invertebrate invasions in the Caspian Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1024050824073" volume="5" year="2003">Grigorovich et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EAF9CD1C019AD503009147D8E25B96EB" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5C5DD813939EFDF227DBE845FEB544F3" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Taxonomic notes. This species has commonly been mentioned as 
<taxonomicName id="A67F42AD1AB13503C5F335A1C572B2B3" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Mytilaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mytilaster lineatus" order="Mytilida" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lineatus">Mytilaster lineatus</taxonomicName>
(Gmelin, 1791), but the Caspian-Aral species lacks the ribbing typical for that species. The attribution to 
<taxonomicName id="ACFB2F9E95864C49C72BB6E3A7152A04" genus="M." lsidName="M. minimus" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" rank="species" species="minimus">M. minimus</taxonomicName>
is based on shell morphology but confirmation from molecular analyses is required.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4EE88B3495C5DBCDCDF51FB3D62F73C0" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="238A311318DF4A5778F973399669C2BD" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Mytilaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mytilaster minimus" order="Mytilida" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minimus">Mytilaster minimus</taxonomicName>
has successfully replaced 
<taxonomicName id="E410DAD47D99AB14B4CE19DBF3F71FAB" class="Bivalvia" family="Dreissenidae" genus="Dreissena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dreissena caspia" order="Myida" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caspia">Dreissena caspia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45C12E779B151F68BFA1BF040D4FD038" genus="D." lsidName="D. elata" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" rank="species" species="elata">D. elata</taxonomicName>
between 1938 and 1957 (
<bibRefCitation id="62287B1102D7FF8D52D82F81305A0093" author="Kostianoy, AG" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin" pageId="77" pageNumber="108" title="The Caspian Sea Environment." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/b138238" year="2005">Kostianoy and Kosarev 2005</bibRefCitation>
) in the Caspian Sea. 
<bibRefCitation id="0527595E568835EB5B0623490A273145" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Logvinenko and Starobogatov (1969)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from the southern areas of the northern Caspian Sea, in the middle and the southern Caspian Sea down to 35-50 m water depth. Rarely, small individuals were found at depths down to 100 m. The species does not tolerate salinities below 7-8‰. This species was mentioned from depths between 200 and 600 m in the South Caspian Basin of Azerbaijan (
<bibRefCitation id="0FA6C51E3A66DBF255307F4E6725EE7D" author="Mirzoev, GS" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Zoological Studies" pageId="79" pageNumber="110" pagination="43 - 48" title="Zoobenthos distribution patterns in the deepwater horizon of Azerbaijan sector of the Caspian Sea." url="http://www.zoologyjournals.com/download/74/1-7-29-696.pdf" volume="2" year="2017">Mirzoev and Alekperov 2017</bibRefCitation>
, who reported the species as 
<taxonomicName id="99114B9306B838AC951C88212370FE0A" genus="M." lsidName="M. lineatus" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" rank="species" species="lineatus">M. lineatus</taxonomicName>
). These deep records are unusual given other records and will require confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
